Module nl.naturalis.common
Package nl.naturalis.common.collection

Class IntArrayList

java.lang.Object
nl.naturalis.common.collection.IntArrayList
All Implemented Interfaces:
IntList
public class IntArrayList
extends Object
implements IntList
A List of int values. The backing array is exposed via the toArray() method, which returns the backing array itself, rather than a copy of it.
Author:
Ayco Holleman

  • Constructor Summary

    Constructors
    Constructor Description
    IntArrayList()
    Creates an IntList with an initial capacity of 10 and doubling it each time it fills up.
    IntArrayList​(int capacity)
    Creates an IntList with the specified initial capacity and doubling it each time it fills up.
    IntArrayList​(int capacity, float enlargeBy, AugmentationType incrementType)  
    IntArrayList​(int capacity, int enlargeBy)
    Creates an IntList with the specified initial capacity and enlarging it by the specified amount of elements each time it fills up.
    IntArrayList​(IntList other)
    Creates a new IntList containing the same integers as the specified IntList.
